I&#39;m not sure what you want to do here, what is `x` and what type does `character` have. It would be nice to have this info in the question. But if you want to check if the char of the string is a unicode digit you can do smth like that (since every `Char` in Kotlin is a unicode char already):

```kotlin
for (uni in string) {
  if (uni in kotlin.text.CharCategory.DECIMAL_DIGIT_NUMBER) {
    finalNumber = uni.toInt() * x + finalNumber
  } else {
